	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64533887"><p>&gt;monopolies are *always* a bad thing.</p><p>Not quite.  *market power* is the bad things, and monopolies usually provide that.</p><p>This, however, is--at least for the moment--a "contestable monopoly".   Someone is on top but either there aren't significant barriers to entry, or there are already other competitors.</p><p>getting a monopoly by building better is legal and not problematic.  *Using* the market power (if any) from the resultant monopoly to stifle the others *is* a problem, and needs to be swiftly stomped.</p><p>AMD is<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

